─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NOTE ON UPSTREAM SOURCES
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This dataset draws on, references, and builds upon other open
scholarly resources, each with its own license:

  - Glottolog 5.2 (Hammarström et al. 2025) — CC BY 4.0
  - Concepticon — CC BY 4.0
  - SIL Comparative African Wordlist (SILCAWL) — see SIL terms

Lexical forms harvested from third-party dictionaries, grammars,
and wordlists remain subject to the copyright of their original
authors and publishers. EALex distributes only metadata, structural
classifications, and lexical data either (a) released under
compatible open licenses, (b) gathered through fair-use comparative
research practices typical of historical linguistics, or
(c) contributed directly under CC BY 4.0 by their original holders.

Researchers and contributors are responsible for ensuring that
data they submit to EALex respects the rights of original sources.
